{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σαλπ-ίζω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <b>-ιῶ</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Num.10.4 \">LXX</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐσάλπιγξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.2.17, 5th-6th c.BC: Archippus Comicus 19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> σάλπιγξα (see. below):—later, <i>future</i> σαλπίσω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Cor.15.52 \">NT</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐσάλπισα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Josh.6.13, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Ocyp.” 114, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 4.130b, etc.:—\">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]<i>passive</i>, <i>perfect</i> σεσάλπιγκται (περι-) Eudamidas cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.13.65\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]:—<b>σαλπίσσω</b> is Tarentine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 1654.24, “Anecdota Graeca - MSS. Bibl. Oxon.” 1.62\">Refs</a>]; <b>σαλπίττω</b> <i>Attic dialect</i>, cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc., 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Jud.Voc.” 10, variant in 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 4.86 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>σαλπίδδω</b> <i>Boeotian dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anecdota Graeca - MSS. Bibl. Oxon.” 4.325\">Refs</a>]:—<b>sound the trumpet</b>, σάλπιγξι ῥυθμοὺς σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.3.32: with _accusative_ _cognate_, σ. πολέμου κτύπον Batrachomyomachia 200; σ. ἀνακλητικόν “Anthologia Graeca” 11.136 (1st c.AD: Lucillius Epigrammaticus); λιγὺν ἦχον 3rd c.BC: Hedylus Epigrammaticus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 11.497d; τὸ.. δείπνου σημεῖον 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 4.130b: _absolutely_, ὅταν ποιῇς ἐλεημοσύνην, μὴ σαλπίσῃς ἔμπροσθέν σου NT.Matt.6.2: _metaphorically_, ἀμφὶ δὲ σάλπιγξεν μέγας οὐρανός\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>] heaven <b